					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10769809#post-4195782</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10769809/scp-4635#post-4195782</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 24 Mar 2019 19:44:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>not_a_seagull</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3009022</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I downvoted this. However, if you fix some things it would be an upvote.</p> <p>First, the summary of the video isn’t scary at all. It basically follows the &quot;it devolves into static&quot; trope. For this, I would take the example of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1981">SCP-1981</a> for creepy media. Instead of having it be a disembodied male voice, have some entity visible to teach the viewer. You could even have a picture of the entity (there’s a lot of good stuff in Wikimedia’s unexplained category if you’re interested). Also, instead of having it go to static, instead have it go the other way into “unteaching” English or something like that. Maybe they even go into the First Language.</p> <p>Secondly, the final document that describes the investigation did nothing for me except to make your GoI less scary. I would get rid of it, and move the introduction of the Church to Orwell’s suicide note. I think that, with some modifications, having it end on that note would be better than the current ending, which leaves very little to the imagination.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
